ZH: 今天又折腾了一天，我真的好累。
EN: I've been busy all day again today, I'm really tired.

ZH: 这个项目折腾了我们好几个月，终于结束了。
EN: This project kept us busy for several months, but it's finally over.

ZH: 他老是折腾着这些乱七八糟的东西，真是让人头疼。
EN: He always messes around with these miscellaneous things, it's really annoying.

ZH: 别折腾了，听我的，这样做才是最好的选择。
EN: Stop messing around, listen to me, this is the best option.

ZH: 他为了折腾这个新餐厅，花了很多时间和金钱。
EN: He spent a lot of time and money on setting up this new restaurant.

ZH: 不要再折腾他了，他已经够受伤的了。
EN: Don't hassle him anymore, he's already hurt enough.

ZH: 别折腾了，放松一下，好好休息。
EN: Don't fuss around, relax and get some rest.

ZH: 为了这次活动，我们整晚都在折腾布置会场。
EN: We spent the whole night setting up the venue for this event.

ZH: 他总是喜欢折腾新玩意，从不满足于现有的东西。
EN: He always likes to play with new things and never content with what he has.

ZH: 这个人就是喜欢折腾，没有一天安静下来的时候。
EN: This person just loves to fiddle around, never has a quiet day.

ZH: 这只猫折腾了好几个小时终于抓住了那只老鼠。
EN: This cat chased around for several hours until it finally caught the mouse.

ZH: 不要再折腾汽车了，你已经修了三次了。
EN: Don't mess around with the car anymore, you've already fixed it three times.

ZH: 他每天都在折腾自己的发型，总要弄得别人都头疼。
EN: He messes around with his hairstyle every day, causing headaches for others.

ZH: 孩子们边吃边玩，折腾了一顿丰盛的晚餐。
EN: The children ate and played, enjoying a lively dinner.

ZH: 这个决定折腾了我们很久，但最终我们还是做出了正确的选择。
EN: This decision troubled us for a long time, but in the end, we made the right choice.

ZH: 这次旅行真是折腾，出了很多意外。
EN: This trip was quite eventful, with many unexpected incidents.

ZH: 別折騰了，我已經跟你說過這個東西壞了。
EN: Stop fussing around, I've already told you this thing is broken.

ZH: 每次搬家都很折騰，希望這次能安定下來。
EN: Moving house is always a hassle, I hope this time we can settle down.

ZH: 為了設計這個產品，我們花了好幾個月時間不斷折騰。
EN: We spent several months constantly tweaking and improving this product's design.

